<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1399,1919,2027]" lastBlockId="13.[189,1399,280,609]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
This subspecies was described based on two males collected by J. Ogilvie at 
<collectingCountry box="[1141,1306,1966,1992]" name="Saint Vincent and the Grenadines" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Saint Vincent</collectingCountry>
, Lesser Antilles, on 
<date box="[330,503,2001,2027]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1938-04-12">April 12, 1938</date>
. In the original description, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cockerell" box="[828,1027,2001,2027]" firstAuthor="Cockerell" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="280 - 283" refId="ref20279" refString="Cockerell T. D. A. 1938. Bees from St. Vincent, British West Indies. The Entomologist 71: 280 - 283." type="journal article" year="1938">Cockerell (1938)</bibRefCitation>
did not specify which male was the 
<typeStatus box="[230,333,280,306]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">holotype</typeStatus>
or mentioned any data that could help to recognize it. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure" box="[1067,1228,280,307]" firstAuthor="Moure" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="97 - 160" refId="ref21372" refString="Moure J. S. 1960. Notes on the types of the Neotropical bees described by Fabricius (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). Studia Entomologica 3 (1 - 4): 97 - 160." type="journal article" year="1960">Moure (1960)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned the type of this species was numbered 54853. In the 
<collectionCode box="[751,844,318,344]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
, both specimens cited by Cockerell were found, with the number mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure" box="[564,733,355,382]" firstAuthor="Moure" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="97 - 160" refId="ref21372" refString="Moure J. S. 1960. Notes on the types of the Neotropical bees described by Fabricius (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). Studia Entomologica 3 (1 - 4): 97 - 160." type="journal article" year="1960">Moure (1960)</bibRefCitation>
, one bearing a label “type” and the other “cotype”. The 
<typeStatus box="[189,292,393,419]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[307,376,393,419]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1268,1294]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,770,1225]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[189,1398,770,1225]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 8. Centris versicolor vincentana Cockerell, 1938, holotype, ♂ (NMNH; USNM ENT 00534218). A. Frontal view. B. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 2 mm. Subgenus Centris (Hemisiella) Moure, 1945" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) has the following data label: 
<collectingCountry box="[728,857,393,419]" name="Saint Vincent and the Grenadines" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">St. Vincent</collectingCountry>
12.4.38 J.O. [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName authority="Ckll" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="versicolor" subSpecies="vincentana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Centris versicolor vincentana</emphasis>
Ckll
</taxonomicName>
Type. [handwritten]\ [red label] Type No 54853 [handwritten] USNM [printed]\ [yellow label] USNM ENT 00534218 [barcode] [printed]\\ DO NOT REMOVE SI DB Reference Not a property tag T. Schultz 
<collectionCode box="[367,457,507,533]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
[printed]. The male 
<typeStatus box="[711,812,507,533]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">paratype</typeStatus>
has the following data label: 
<collectingCountry box="[1179,1311,506,533]" name="Saint Vincent and the Grenadines" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">St. Vincent</collectingCountry>
B.W.I. 12.4.38 (J. Ogilvie) [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName authority="Ckll" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1938" box="[601,1009,544,571]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="versicolor" subSpecies="vincentana">
<emphasis box="[601,951,544,571]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Centris versicolor vincentana</emphasis>
Ckll
</taxonomicName>
cotype [handwritten]\ [red label] 
<typeStatus box="[189,292,582,608]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Paratype</typeStatus>
No 54853 [handwritten] USNM [printed]. Both specimens are in good condition.
</paragraph>
